    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;The Extensible Authentication Protocol (EAP) provides a standard mechanism for support of various authentication methods.  This document defines the Command-Codes and AVPs necessary to carry EAP packets between a Network Access Server (NAS) and a back-end authentication server. [STANDARDS-TRACK]&lt;/p&gt;</t>
